<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="286" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="47.[816,1421,256,376]" pageId="47" pageNumber="286">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[816,935,256,280]" pageId="47" pageNumber="286">Etymology</emphasis>
: The name is a Latin noun in the genitive plural and denotes “of the White Mountains”. It alludes to the fact that the distribution is probably confined to the Lefka Ori (English: White Mountains).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="286" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="47.[816,1421,415,888]" pageId="47" pageNumber="286">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[816,946,415,439]" pageId="47" pageNumber="286">Description</emphasis>
: External characters as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Assing &amp; Brachat &amp; Meybohm" authorityYear="2019" box="[1239,1371,416,440]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Faronus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meybohmi">
<emphasis box="[1239,1371,416,440]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="286">F. meybohmi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Assing &amp; Brachat &amp; Meybohm" authorityYear="2019" box="[816,987,448,472]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Faronus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lefkamontium">
<emphasis box="[816,987,448,472]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="286">F. lefkamontium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, except as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[816,1421,415,888]" pageId="47" pageNumber="286">
Body length 
<quantity box="[957,1086,480,504]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.55" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="47" pageNumber="286" unit="mm" value="1.55" valueMax="1.6" valueMin="1.5">1.5–1.6 mm</quantity>
. Head 
<quantity box="[1164,1317,480,504]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" metricValueMax="2.4" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="47" pageNumber="286" unit="mm" value="0.22999999999999998" valueMax="0.24" valueMin="0.22">0.22–0.24 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[816,969,512,536]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" metricValueMax="3.4" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="47" pageNumber="286" unit="mm" value="0.33" valueMax="0.34" valueMin="0.32">0.32–0.34 mm</quantity>
broad; temples rectangularly projecting, apically with a small circular impression. Eyes large, distinctly convex. Antenna 
<quantity box="[1120,1273,576,600]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.7" metricValueMax="5.8" metricValueMin="5.6" pageId="47" pageNumber="286" unit="mm" value="0.57" valueMax="0.58" valueMin="0.56">0.56–0.58 mm</quantity>
long. Pronotum 
<quantity box="[880,1033,608,632]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.6" pageId="47" pageNumber="286" unit="mm" value="0.27" valueMax="0.28" valueMin="0.26">0.26–0.28 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[1180,1333,608,632]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4499999999999997" metricValueMax="3.5999999999999996" metricValueMin="3.3000000000000003" pageId="47" pageNumber="286" unit="mm" value="0.345" valueMax="0.36" valueMin="0.33">0.33–0.36 mm</quantity>
broad, significantly longer and slightly broader than head. Elytra 
<quantity box="[816,969,672,696]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" metricValueMax="2.9" metricValueMin="2.7" pageId="47" pageNumber="286" unit="mm" value="0.28" valueMax="0.29" valueMin="0.27">0.27–0.29 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[1083,1236,672,696]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.35" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="4.2" pageId="47" pageNumber="286" unit="mm" value="0.435" valueMax="0.45" valueMin="0.42">0.42–0.45 mm</quantity>
broad, 1.5 times as broad as long. Hind wings completely reduced.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[816,1421,415,888]" pageId="47" pageNumber="286">
♂: metatrochanter ventrally with a knife-shaped dilatation; metatibia with a small apical spine; femora unmodified, not dilated; aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1248,1335,800,824]" captionStart="Figs 156–173" captionStartId="16.[213,253,1979,2001]" captionTargetBox="[230,1455,259,1961]" captionTargetId="figure-173@16.[223,1455,255,1972]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figs 156–173: Amauronyx chanianus (156), A. occidens (157),A. askifouicus (158), Bryaxismeybohmianus (159–161), Bythinus creticus (162–163), Euplectus assingi(164),Faronus meybohmi (165), F.lefkamontium (166),F.albimontium(167),Tychus chanianus (168), and Sepedophilus creticus (169–173): aedeagus in dorsal and ventral view (156–158, 160, 163–168, 172); antennomeres I–II (159); internal structures of aedeagus (161); maxillary palpomere IV (162); habitus (169); male sternite VIII (170); male tergites IX–X (171); apical portion of aedeagus (173). Scale bars: 169: 1.0 mm; 170–172: 0.2 mm; 156–161, 163–168, 173: 0.1 mm; 162 without scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4755276" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4755276/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="286">Fig. 167</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.05" metricValueMax="3.1" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="47" pageNumber="286" unit="mm" value="0.305" valueMax="0.31" valueMin="0.3">0.30– 0.31 mm</quantity>
long; right paramere with one, left paramere with two apical setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[816,1421,927,1048]" pageId="47" pageNumber="286">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[816,1023,927,952]" pageId="47" pageNumber="286">Comparative notes</emphasis>
: Among the Cretan representatives of the genus, this species is characterized particularly by the shape of the head, shorter elytra, and by the male primary and secondary sexual characters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="286" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="47.[816,1422,1087,1208]" pageId="47" pageNumber="286">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[816,1176,1087,1112]" pageId="47" pageNumber="286">Distribution and natural history</emphasis>
: Like 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Assing &amp; Brachat &amp; Meybohm" authorityYear="2019" box="[1245,1415,1088,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Faronus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lefkamontium">
<emphasis box="[1245,1415,1088,1112]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="286">F. lefkamontium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Assing &amp; Brachat &amp; Meybohm" authorityYear="2019" box="[816,975,1120,1144]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Faronus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albimontium">
<emphasis box="[816,975,1120,1144]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="286">F. albimontium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recorded only from the environs of Omalos in the Lefka Ori. The specimens were sifted from litter and grass roots at altitudes of 1060 and 
<quantity box="[1336,1416,1184,1208]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="47" pageNumber="286" unit="m" value="1200.0">1200 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
